00:00:21.119 --> 00:00:27.179
One of the main arguments people make against video games is that they prime kids to be violent.

00:00:27.369 --> 00:00:33.718
Priming is a non-conscious form of memory where one stimulus influences the response to a subsequent stimulus.

00:00:33.719 --> 00:00:36.989
For example, if I said the word yellow then asked you to name a fruit

00:00:36.989 --> 00:00:39.480
you would most likely say banana.

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:40.580
This led to a study in which

00:00:40.660 --> 00:00:43.760
researchers had participants play one of two games.

00:00:43.760 --> 00:00:46.840
One game where they were in a car avoiding collisions.

00:00:46.840 --> 00:00:49.820
Another where they were just a mouse avoiding a cat.

00:00:49.820 --> 00:00:53.900
Following the game, the researchers, based on priming, hypothesized

00:00:53.910 --> 00:00:58.480
the players would be faster at categorizing objects associated with the game they played,

00:00:58.480 --> 00:00:59.669
more quickly in the real world.

00:00:59.670 --> 00:01:05.640
So the players looked at pictures of things like a bus or a dog and were asked to quickly label them either as a vehicle

00:01:05.640 --> 00:01:10.290
or an animal. Those who played the car game were no faster at categorizing vehicles.

00:01:10.290 --> 00:01:13.799
And those who played the cat game were no faster at categorizing animals.

00:01:13.800 --> 00:01:18.520
In fact, those who played each game had a slower reaction time to the related category.

00:01:18.520 --> 00:01:21.820
Meaning negative priming might actually be occurring.

