00:01:26.979 --> 00:01:30.059
today's game designers are capable of producing incredible graphics.

00:01:30.660 --> 00:01:36.640
Therefore another criticism is the more realistic a game the more likely it will activate aggressive behavior.

00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:41.300
To study this concept, one study had participants play one of two Kombat games.

00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:45.040
One where the characters were modeled using rag doll physics:

00:01:45.060 --> 00:01:50.560
movements modeled off of the human skeleton, which means they had very physically realistic death behaviors.

00:01:50.579 --> 00:01:53.820
The other game used deaths that were extremely unrealistic.

00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:56.879
Afterwards, aggression was assessed via a word association

00:01:57.280 --> 00:02:02.040
test and the game with the more realistic deaths showed no increase in aggression.

00:02:02.180 --> 00:02:06.800
Of the available research, most find no link between video games and violence.

00:02:06.880 --> 00:02:11.460
